<div class="post-date">Jul 14</div>
<h2><a https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.html?id=1105" title="New Music Thursday"> New Music Thursday</a></h2>

<div class="entry">


     

  	<p>I bought some new CDs for the first time in probably years. I had been promising Darlene some new jazz for a while and now that I&#8217;ve played a few tracks I think I chose well. Here&#8217;s what I snagged from <br />
<a href="http://www.houseohits.com/hoh/index.htm">House O&#8217; Hits Records</a>...</p>
	<ul>
	<li><strong>Stay Loose&#8230;Jimmy Smith Sings Again</strong>: This guy is great on the Hammond B3 organ. One of his better albums from the 1960s.</li>
		<li><strong>The Definitive Chet Baker</strong>: So far I like his trumpet better than his vocals, but not bad when he combines the two. I bought this one on a whim.</li>
		<li><strong>Compact Jazz Lionel Hampton</strong>: This is not one of the better Hampton collections, but I love him on the vibraphone. Hey it was a used CD.</li>
	</ul>

	<p>The test obviously is whether she&#8217;ll like them&#8230;</p>



 
<div class="line"></div>

<div class="smallcat">Posted in <a https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.html?c=Culture">Culture</a></div>
<div class="smalluser"> by <a https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.html?author=E.G.+Yarnetsky">E.G. Yarnetsky</a></div>
