<div class="post-date">Jul  3</div>
<h2><a https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.html?id=1101" title="Organic groceries in Madison!"> Organic groceries in Madison!</a></h2>

<div class="entry">


     

  	<p>Madison has joined the big leagues of food. A new grocery open here downtown that offers organic food, fruit, vegatables, meats and cheeses. The variety is wonderful.</p>

	<p>Check out <a href="http://www.localharvestmarket.com">Local Harvest Market</a>. They&#8217;re planning an &#8220;e-market&#8221; that will open soon so you can get an idea of what they&#8217;re carrying.</p>

	<p>What amazes me is they even have FRESH fish flown in from the coast three times a week. I don&#8217;t know the last time I&#8217;ve had fresh fish. Also every kind of meat you can imagine&#8212;we can even get bison, rabbit and duck. If you have the opportunity, you should try organic free-range chicken eggs. They really are pretty amazing.</p>

	<p>They also have prepared meals. We had beef curry rice for dinner tonight. They also had grilled swordfish with pineapple and mango sauce. They&#8217;ll even make you sandwiches from fresh baked bread and premium Boar&#8217;s Head meats from their deli cut to order. I&#8217;m told sushi is also coming soon.</p>

	<p>I know one of the people who will be working there and she said they all attended workshops to learn about the products they&#8217;ll be selling. Indeed, she attended a fullday on just wines and cheeses.</p>

	<p>While I doubt I could afford to buy all my food there, but I am very much looking forward to sampling the fare, this will be fun&#8212;real food!</p>



 
<div class="line"></div>

<div class="smallcat">Posted in <a https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.html?c=Life">Life</a></div>
