<div class="post-date">Jun  9</div>
<h2><a https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.html?id=1094" title="Yesterday? homework. Today? homework. Tomorrow?"> Yesterday? homework. Today? homework. Tomorrow?</a></h2>

<div class="entry">


     

  	<p>Well, tomorrow is class, but the day after that will be homework too.</p>

	<p>I&#8217;m coming up on the end of my first summer session and I&#8217;m amazed at how much information is being squeezed into the short space. Having taken two 16-week courses and now one six-week course&#8212;I&#8217;d prefer quarters over semesters and summer sessions. I think the class is going pretty well, though I&#8217;m behind on the reading (what else is new).</p>

	<p>Unfortunately, Mother Nature is not helping me much here.</p>

	<p>We managed to get air conditioning in our building for the first time just as it hit 94.8 her downtown this week. However, I&#8217;d love to know what tree, mold or mite is doing me in. I&#8217;m having an extreme allergic reaction to something. I&#8217;m wanting to tear my eyes out and it feels like I&#8217;m breathing hot sands into my lungs.</p>

	<p>Some prescription eye drops I had left over from last summer&#8217;s allergy attack helped, but Claritin wasn&#8217;t doing the trick so I went in to see the doctor today.</p>

	<p>He didn&#8217;t tell me anything I didn&#8217;t already know&#8212;I&#8217;m joining the thousands who are suffering from the Ohio River Valley Crud. ORVC is a catch-all malady that is suffered at vaying times of year by valley residents. It typifies the valley as a cauldron of allergies and sinus junk.</p>

	<p>Mind you, I didn&#8217;t like the prescription&#8212;my insurance charged me $40 for Zyrtec-D and I have to take corticosteroid hormone junk for my lungs starting in the morning. While I really didn&#8217;t like the side effect from the last time I had to take the stuff, I&#8217;ll take that over not breathing. It&#8217;s indeed like the billboard about asthma, it is kind of like being a fish out of water.</p>



 
<div class="line"></div>

<div class="smallcat">Posted in <a https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.html?c=Life">Life</a></div>
<div class="smalluser"> by <a https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.html?author=E.G.+Yarnetsky">E.G. Yarnetsky</a></div>
