<div class="post-date">May 29</div>
<h2><a https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.html?id=1092" title="Wanderlust and Memorial Day weekend"> Wanderlust and Memorial Day weekend</a></h2>

<div class="entry">


     

  	<p>When Darlene and I were in college we wandered just about every road in western Ohio. Once we got out of college, other than vacation, we lost the wanderlust.</p>

	<p>But now that I&#8217;m driving back and forth to Indy every week I&#8217;ve regained my wanderlust. There&#8217;s only so many times you can drive down I-65 without getting sick of it. There&#8217;s just something satisfying about being on the road not yet traveled.</p>

	<p>As a result I&#8217;m finding about every way to drive from Indy to Madison. So far I&#8217;d say my favorite is Indiana 3 between Greensburg and North Vernon. It was a very &#8220;springy-Hoosierish&#8221; day. Barns sitting out in deep green rolling fields. Just nice.</p>

	<p>After class on Friday, we went to visit Darlene&#8217;s family near Lima, Ohio, for the holiday. We drove up from Indy to Marion and then went straight east through the flat farmlands of eastern Indiana. The fields were huge, going from the road back at least a mile in every direction before you hit a stand of trees. Wheat fields are starting to grow.</p>

	<p>We crossed into Ohio going over the Wabash River (yes Hoosiers, it starts in Ohio) and over to Grand Lake St. Mary&#8217;s. The largest inland lake in Ohio, it was created to be the resevoir for the Miami-Erie Canal. The lake is an impossible blue. I&#8217;d only seen photos that blue somewhere in the Caribbean. The lake is flanked by Celina and St. Mary&#8217;s, Both are nice towns. Celina is the resort town of the two with nice homes and condos line the lake. St. Mary&#8217;s was the canal town with fragments of the Miami-Erie still flowing through town.</p>

	<p>It&#8217;s great to wander. It helps cures the urge to runaway from home when I need to be studying.</p>

	<p>The weekend has been fun. I have managed to get a chunk of reading for class done, but we&#8217;ve also done a good share of partying with her family.</p>

	<p>We went to a &#8220;school&#8217;s out for summer&#8221; party at Darlene&#8217;s sister&#8217;s house and helped watch about 40 kids party. Two of her sister&#8217;s kids are in a hard rock garage band and heard them play last night. Of course, they were indeed playing in the garage. They were really good considering the oldest was only 15.</p>

	<p>Today about half the family came out to her parents&#8217; house. Two of my brothers-in-law and I played a couple hours of frisbee golf. Here&#8217;s a typical hole for us&#8230; We&#8217;d start from the bed of Stan&#8217;s pickup truck, throw down across the back field into a dried pond, back across the barley field and into the compost bin, back up the field and into the corn wagon bin finally tosing the frisbee through the front window of the pickup to complete the hole. I had a 15 on that hole. We didn&#8217;t play a par anything the whole game.</p>

	<p>Toss in a really moist turkey and two pretty decent car races and it&#8217;s a been a pretty good Memorial Day weekend. Mind you I have another chunk of homework before we&#8217;ll head home tomorrow.</p>



 
<div class="line"></div>

